header.gameNote: MIDEAST REGION AT UNIVERSITY PARK PA

article.description: Kelly Mazzante started slow, but heated up to score 27 points and lead Penn State over Holy Cross.
article.headline: Mazzante makes up for late start
article.linkText: Mazzante scores 27 to lead Penn State past Holy Cross
article.story:
STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Kelly Mazzante scored 27 points as
Penn State beat Holy Cross 64-33 in the first round of the Mideast
Regional on Sunday.

	   It took Mazzante almost seven minutes to make her first shot, a
fade-away 19-footer. After that, she went on a tear, hitting three
fast break layups and a 3-pointer from the right wing during a 17-2
run that made it 28-7 nearly six minutes before halftime.

	   She finished the half with 19 points on 8-of-14 shooting, and
outscored Holy Cross herself as the fourth-seeded Lady Lions (25-8)
led 38-16 at halftime.

	   No. 13 seed Holy Cross (24-8) never got closer than 22 points in
the second half, and its 33 points were the least by a Holy Cross
team since a 55-32 loss to Lafayette in 1992.

	   Penn State will face No. 5 seed South Carolina in the second
round Tuesday. The Gamecocks beat Chattanooga 68-54 to advance.

	   Jessica Brungo, who was not expected to play because of a foot
injury, finished with 12 points and eight rebounds for the Lady
Lions, and Tanisha Wright scored 10.

	   Lisa Andrews led Holy Cross with 10 points.
